cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL 

The paper focuses on specifying database management systems (DBMS) using the RM-ODP framework, which is a standard for open distributed processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.SE (Software Engineering) as the paper discusses the engineering language and structure of DBMS. The paper also touches upon distributed systems and inter-working, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions an object model and architecture, which could relate to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
